#: ../../content/index.md:1
msgid "Welcome to the Resthome documentation"
msgstr "Welkom bij de Resthome-documentatie"

#: ../../content/index.md:4
msgid ""
"User documentation for the Resthome software (on Odoo) for nursing and care "
"homes (MR/MRS): residents, care, INAMI billing, eFact, MDA, eAgreement."
msgstr ""
"Gebruikersdocumentatie van de Resthome-software (op Odoo) voor "
"woonzorgcentra (WZC/RVT): bewoners, zorg, RIZIV-facturatie, eFact, MDA, "
"eAgreement."

#: ../../content/index.md:7
msgid ""
"**Resthome** is the management software for **nursing homes (MR)** and "
"**nursing and care homes (MRS)**, published by LPLG **on Odoo** — residents,"
" care, meals, INAMI/mutuality billing and the Belgian eHealth exchanges "
"(eFact, MDA, eAgreement), all in one place. This documentation guides you "
"day by day, step by step, with screenshots."
msgstr ""
"**Resthome** is de beheersoftware voor **rustoorden (ROB)** en **rust- en "
"verzorgingstehuizen (RVT)**, uitgegeven door LPLG **op Odoo** — bewoners, "
"zorg, maaltijden, RIZIV/mutualiteitsfacturatie en de Belgische eHealth-"
"uitwisselingen (eFact, MDA, eAgreement), allemaal op één plek. Deze "
"documentatie begeleidt u dagelijks, stap voor stap, met schermafbeeldingen."

#: ../../content/index.md:17
msgid "Getting started"
msgstr "Aan de slag"

#: ../../content/index.md:18
msgid ""
"Log in, discover the apps and the dashboard, and find your way around a "
"screen."
msgstr ""
"Aanmelden, de toepassingen en het dashboard ontdekken, en uw weg vinden in "
"een scherm."

#: ../../content/index.md:21
msgid "The billing journey"
msgstr "Het facturatietraject"

#: ../../content/index.md:22
msgid ""
"The big picture: admission → MDA → eAgreement → Katz → eFact → payment."
msgstr "Het overzicht: opname → MDA → eAgreement → Katz → eFact → betaling."

#: ../../content/index.md:25
msgid "Residents"
msgstr "Bewoners"

#: ../../content/index.md:26
msgid ""
"Admission, stay, Katz and geriatric assessments, rooms and the condition "
"report."
msgstr ""
"Opname, verblijf, Katz- en geriatrische evaluaties, kamers en de "
"plaatsbeschrijving."

#: ../../content/index.md:29
msgid "Billing"
msgstr "Facturatie"

#: ../../content/index.md:30
msgid "Billing periods, INAMI packages, supplements, absences and invoices."
msgstr ""
"Facturatieperiodes, RIZIV-forfaits, supplementen, afwezigheden en facturen."

#: ../../content/index.md:33
msgid "eHealth"
msgstr "eHealth"

#: ../../content/index.md:34
msgid ""
"Insurability (MDA), electronic invoicing (eFact) and agreements "
"(eAgreement)."
msgstr ""
"Verzekerbaarheid (MDA), elektronische facturatie (eFact) en akkoorden "
"(eAgreement)."

#: ../../content/index.md:37
msgid "Care"
msgstr "Zorg"

#: ../../content/index.md:38
msgid "Clinical record, prescriptions, care plans and clinical registers."
msgstr "Medisch dossier, voorschriften, zorgplannen en klinische registers."

#: ../../content/index.md:41
msgid "Meals"
msgstr "Maaltijden"

#: ../../content/index.md:42
msgid ""
"Menus and diets, meal distribution, nutrition monitoring and the family "
"portal."
msgstr ""
"Menu's en diëten, maaltijdverdeling, voedingsopvolging en het "
"familieportaal."

#: ../../content/index.md:45
msgid "Resident documents"
msgstr "Documenten van de bewoner"

#: ../../content/index.md:46
msgid "Automatic document folders per resident and attachment centralization."
msgstr ""
"Automatische documentmappen per bewoner en centralisatie van bijlagen."

#: ../../content/index.md:49
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr "Configuratie"

#: ../../content/index.md:50
msgid "All the settings: residents, billing, eHealth, meals and documents."
msgstr ""
"Alle instellingen: bewoners, facturatie, eHealth, maaltijden en documenten."

#: ../../content/index.md:54
msgid "A precise question?"
msgstr "Een precieze vraag?"

#: ../../content/index.md:57
msgid ""
"Use the **search bar** at the top, the **[FAQ](faq.md)** or the "
"**[Glossary](glossaire.md)**. This documentation is public and written to be"
" readable by AI assistants — you can ask your question in plain language."
msgstr ""
"Gebruik de **zoekbalk** bovenaan, de **[FAQ](faq.md)** of de "
"**[Woordenlijst](glossaire.md)**. Deze documentatie is openbaar en "
"geschreven om leesbaar te zijn voor AI-assistenten — u kunt uw vraag in "
"gewone taal stellen."

